<div id="classic-to-spa-request-info-display">
    <div id="spified-mode">
        <h3>the sample is in spified mode</h3>
        <p>In the spified mode, this side bar never reloads on inner-site navigation as only a part of the DOM, the <i>load content</i>, is fetched.</p>
        <p>
            The sample can be switched between working as a SPA or a classic web application by controlling a cookie. The change is entirely client side: The behavior of the server
            is independent from the cookie setting.
        </p>
        <p><a href="#">Click here to switch to classic mode.</a></p>
    </div>

    <div id="classic-mode">
        <h3>the sample is in classic mode</h3>
        <p>In the classic mode, the sample application behaves like a classic web application and this side bar as well as jQuery is reloaded on every inner-site navigation.</p>
        <p>
            The sample can be switched between working as a SPA or a classic web application by controlling a cookie. The change is entirely client side: The behavior of the server
            is independent from the cookie setting.
        </p>
        <p><a href="#">Click here to switch to spified mode.</a></p>
    </div>

    <script>
        (function () {
            var element = document.getElementById(
                Cookies.get('use-classic-mode') ? 'spified-mode' : 'classic-mode');
            element.remove();
            $('#spified-mode a').on('click', function () { ClassicToSpa.setClassicMode(true); window.document.location.reload(); });
            $('#classic-mode a').on('click', function () { ClassicToSpa.setClassicMode(false); window.document.location.reload(); });
        })();
    </script>
</div>
